libwk2gtkpdf for Debian
-----------------------

Headless Operation & Xvfb Service
=================================

This library is designed to automatically handle headless environments. 
If no $DISPLAY environment variable is detected, the library will attempt 
to start the 'xvfb.service' provided by the wkgtk-html2pdf-common package.

To enable this automated startup without root privileges, the calling 
user must be a member of the 'xvfb' system group:

    sudo usermod -aG xvfb <username>

After adding the user to the group, a logout/login (or a new shell 
session) is required for the changes to take effect.

Rendering Engine (GTK4/WebKit6)
===============================

When running via the xvfb.service, the environment is forced to use 
software rendering (GSK_RENDERER=software) to ensure compatibility 
across all server environments, including those without a GPU.

Customization
=============

If you need to override the default Xvfb resolution or rendering 
settings, do not edit the system service directly. Instead, use 
a systemd drop-in file:

    sudo systemctl edit xvfb.service

